quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
29,24,"The people {1} (of Abraham) had no other answer than to say: “Kill him or burn him.” {2} But Allah delivered him from the fire. {3} There are many Signs in this for those who believe. {4}",footnotes:1:From here the discourse again turns to the story of the Prophet Abraham (peace be upon him).“Indeed
29,25,"He said: {1} “You have taken up idols instead of Allah as a bond of love among yourselves {2} in the present life, but on the Day of Resurrection you will disown and curse one another. {3} Your refuge shall be the Fire, and none will come to your aid.”",footnotes:1:The Prophet Abraham (peace be upon him) must have said this after his safe deliverance from the fire.That is
29,26,"Then did Lot believe him, {1} and Abraham said: “I am emigrating unto my Lord. {2} He is All-Powerful, All-Wise,” {3}",footnotes:1:The context shows that when the Prophet Abraham (peace be upon him) came out of the fire and spoke the preceding sentences
29,27,"and We bestowed upon him (offspring like) Isaac and Jacob, {1} and bestowed prophethood and the Book {2} on his descendants and granted him his reward in this world; he will certainly be among the righteous {3} in the Hereafter.",footnotes:1:The Prophet Isaac (peace be upon him) was his son and the Prophet Jacob (peace be upon him) was the grandson. The other sons of the Prophet Abraham (peace be upon him) have not been mentioned here
29,28,"We sent Lot {1} and he said to his people: “You commit the abomination that none in the world ever committed before you.",footnotes:1:For comparison
29,29,"What! Do you go to men {1} (to satisfy your lust), engage in highway robbery, and commit evil deeds in your gatherings?” {2} Then they had no answer to offer other than to say: “Bring Allah's chastisement upon us if you are truthful.”",footnotes:1:That is
29,30,"Lot said: “My Lord, aid me against these mischievous people.”"
